Employment records at Kenyatta University point to ethnic bigotry, Auditor General Edward Ouko’s report indicates. Ouko, in his 2016/2017 audit report, revealed a worrying trend in staffing at the university which should be guided by the National Cohesion and Integration Act, 2008. The Act provides that no public funded institution shall have more than one-third of its staff from same ethnic extraction. “A review of the university staff data as of 30 June 2017 revealed that one ethnic community accounted for 45 per cent of senior management, 39 percent academic staff and 42 percent on non-teaching staff,” Ouko’s report says. Click here for the latest political
news 